    <stitle>STEERABLE DRIVE AXLE END UNIT: FABCO - ADJUSTMENTS - TOE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>TOE</title>
        <para>Since the SDA-1200, 1400, and 1600 axles use an offset tie rod tube, adjustment is made by turning a small
            adjuster located at the left end of the tie rod tube (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0201122">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0201122" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0201122" filename="../figg02/g0201122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 22. Toe Adjuster</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>To adjust toe, loosen the tie rod adjuster clamp and left tie rod clamp. Rotate the adjuster until a
            proper setting is achieved. After adjustment, tighten both clamp bolts to 75 ft-lbs. (102 N&#183;m).
        </para>
    </svcproc>
